author: JOCELYN NOVECK
description: Forty-eight years after she gave her first commencement address at Wellesley College, Hillary Clinton returns on Friday to offer another â€” and once again, she's at a crossroads in her life. The first time, she was 21 years old and eager to take on life's adventures, a graduating senior whose bold speech delighted her classmates, dismayed the school's president, and made it into Life magazine. The Hillary who will speak this year on Severance Green Lawn is the battle-scarred politician who came agonizingly close to becoming the first female president of the United States.
title: As Clinton emerges from the woods, what will her role be?
